<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Hrm. If you want to space out your nukes evenly and hover near full mana, why not just toss a nuke every time you hit, say, around 80% mana. That way, your damage is evenly spaced out along time, and achieves the effect you desire.<P>If you want my opinion on the topic, I think instead of trying to do 16% to every mob, you should try to do a bigger percentage of the damage to stronger mobs and a lesser percentage of the damage to weaker mobs.<P>For instance, in LGuk LMH, wizards and names are the targets you want to chain nuke on, but if none of those show up, you would want to do like 32% of the damage to boks, 16% of the damage to dars, and 0% of the damage to zols and wans.<P>That way you play to the strengths of storing up damage and your group would take less damage overall than if you did 16% of the damage to all the knights.<P>Arlina<P>Arlina
</FONT>
