To Arlina <P>I realize that this stratagy is not actually the most benifical over time to a group. This is simply a stratagy designed so you can actually do something each pull instead of doing nothing 40 to 60% of the time. I think most players who have not played a wizared or mag dont have any idea what we do or what we are good for. All they see is some guy stitting 90% of the time and saying is is oom every 4 or 5 pulls. Then they have to run to the rescue every time the mob agroes on him for more than 5 seconds. Even when we do save a group from an over pull this is usually soon forgotten and the image of the sleeping wizard remains.<P> This stratagy is something close to another stratagy I read about in a few other posts called "the spectical". The idea of "the spectical" stratagy is that you use your lvl 1 to lvl 12 spells at lvl 50+ becuase the group has know idea how much damage you do anyway. Basically you just put on a light show every pull by chain casting you lvl 1 spells, this way the group sees you doing something ( even though you are actually doing nothing ) and you still remain FM at all times. Then when there is an over pull you jump in with your best spells and burn down the mob. The people who use this tactic claim that no one seems to notice that they arnt doing any real damage and that they often get praised for all their nuking even though they probably only did a total of 80dmg to a mob with 4000hp.
</FONT>
