I've tried what you suggest in the past Woeful and I must admit it is very hard to control agro. Mobs have an agro list and we can not be near the top of that, simply because we don't have the AC or HP's to backup being pounded on. Casting a level 12 nuke or level 55 nuke will still agro the mob because Spells have a special agro ingrediant. So chain casting a level 20 nuke 10 times is gonna get your head ripped off, piss off the healer who's now healing you more then the tanks, and the tank will feel sorry cause he couldn't taunt right.<P>Sit yer tush down, do your most effective Nuke, mix in rains and keep the pase with the Cleric and or Enchanter. Speaking of the Enchanter you are their body guard. If the puller has 3 mobs incoming and you're sitting on your ass while the chanter is mezzing you are worthless. I have 3 assist buttons. 1 for the main melee, 1 for the Cleric, and 1 for the enchanter. When the Enchanter selects a mob to be mezzed I root it, if both roots and mez fail, I stun it. If the Cleric gets aggroed, I root/stun that mob and move on to nukes if it's time too. Woeful you are thinking about the Wizard the wrong way, we can not and will not ever be the main damage output of the group. Eventually you will discover what I am talking about for yourself, and you'll realize that making an effort to assist the groups other members do their job far outweighs 16% per mob. The less the Cleric/Healer needs to heal means the better of a job you are doing keeping mobs off the people who are not meant to me hit (you, cleric, chanter and even the shaman or other int casters too). I can do all this, and still toss in a drought or 2 per mob. When I was lower in level I had to nuke a little less because spells were not as efficient as Draughts are, but I still played my part I just detailed.<P>--------------------<P>Baelzharon Hopeslayer<BR>Wizard of the 54th Book of Power<BR>BANG! BOOM! POOF!, Done! "WTF" you looking at? PULL SOME MORE<BR>Member of <BR> <A HREF="