Woeful,<BR>Thank you - I was working on a similar spreadsheet, and here you've done all the work for me.  <P>Everyone else,<BR>Think about this for a second.  In a six-person group, if you're doing one-sixth the damage of each mob, by most lights you're pulling your weight.  If a wizard can do this, the groups will feel better about having you there, you'll feel like you're contributing something besides filling out the sixth spot for the xp bonus, and you'll still have at least 80 percent mana when you run into something that needs a full burn.  <P>I routinely sit through greens; the group frequently tells me to save the mana.  I also nuke more heavily on the casters and healers, doing well more than 16% - I HATE healers.  So long as it evens out in the long run, you're helping the group, and in a tangible way (like most others here, I'd rather solo than join a group and do the Spectacle BS.)  <P>Rhian B'Zorch<BR>30th Wizard<BR>Order of the Jade Dragon<BR>Xegony
