<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Bael,<BR>I enjoyed the way you didn't read the above posts, lambasted the idea, and told us we need to grow up.  We're looking at new ideas, trying to find a better way to do our job.  You're mocking people trying to find a better way and preaching the same old line that has done NOTHING for the reputation of wizards since the game left beta.<P>Well, I agree that I need to grow up as a wizard - but excuse me, I hunt Chardok and KC and Velks.... with my level 50 Enchanter.  And as an experienced Enchanter, who until recently had both of the top 2 aggro-producing spells in the game (Allure and Tashania, before CH was changed), I think I might have some small inkling about how crowd control and aggro work.  <BR>Yes, spells do a lot of aggro.  So does taunt.  And we're talking about specialized situations - obviously we're going to be doing something else than carefully metering 16 percent damage if the cleric is being beaten on or the enchanter is getting turned to elf paste. <BR>But on, say, a triple pull where the tanks are pasting one and the enchanter has the other two on hold and the cleric is whistling while Celestial goes off, it's much better for a wizard to contribue his fair share of the damage to the current target - and be able to do the same to the second, and the third - than to sit on your duff through the second two after blasting away at the first. Given Woeful's suggestion, you could contribute to this situation and sit down at 60 percent mana, everyone knows you helped and you still have a significant reserve for when the next emergency shows up.... or you can blow 40 percent on the first mob, 40 percent on the second and have the group wondering why you sat through the third.<P>Consider this...  if you wait for a mob to go to half and nuke it to being a runner (standard wizard tactic) you'll do about 30 percent damage to it (assuming most mobs run at 20 percent - some do more, some less).  This is unsustainable over more than two mobs, so you sit through the third and pray there are no adds.  Or you can do 16 percent to three or four or five mobs (assuming an average 45 second spacing as Woeful calculates) and do 84 percent of the total damage instead of 60.. to more mobs..  and have a reserve left for those unwelcome callers.<P>So instead of criticizing those trying to find a better way of doing things, why don't you see what you can contribute?<P>SoulFrost DeDanaan<BR>50th Enchanter<BR>Rhian B'Zorch<BR>30th Wizard<BR>Order of the Jade Dragon<BR>Xegony
</FONT>
