Helping with the hijacking of the thread...<P>>He seemed to suggest that wizard ac/hp potential is highest of the pure casters<P>Necromancers may sometimes have low AC, but the gear they can get gives them the potential for the most AC if they want it. Because Verant loves to stick them on things that SKs can use, they have a number of choices of gear with decent AC (not to mention other good stats) that the rest of the int casters can't use.<P>Like the night I was in DN and these dropped:<P>Flayed Paebala Leggings   <BR>LORE ITEM MAGIC ITEM NO DROP  <BR>AC: +15 Int: +6 Disease Resist: +20 HP: +20 Mana: +20  <BR>Weight: 2.0 <BR>Classes: Necromancer Ranger Shaman Druid Cleric Paladin Shadowknight Bard Monk Rogue Warrior<BR>Races: All Races   <BR> <BR>Wouldn't have minded being able to wear them, but of course, Necro's are the only int casters that can.<P>Also a 28 AC tunic they can get in there if they want amongst other things. So I would say potentialwise, it would be Necro's for highest AC if they want it.<P><BR>On the topic of the original thread, if you have space to mem low level spells just so you can cast them at the beginning of a fight (talking 50+ here) you are limiting yourself more than you might think. You can control agro without sending your mana efficiency all to hell.
