<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I have approximatly 2700 mana right now. In XP groups the main nukes I use is a Draught and Tears of Druzil (Single Pulls only). On a 3 mob pull, say I am at fm.<P>3 x 215 = 645 mana first mob and done 1800+ points, throw in a stun or 2 and I've gon ethrough 700 mana.<P>Next mob, sit and med till it's at 60% halth, and throw in a stun or 2 at it. Then I toss  my 3 draughts, but I medded a good portion of the first mob back, I'm probably at around 65-70% mana.<P>Last mob, Tears + draught and I sit down at 50% mana medding for the next pull. Most likely the cleric, chanter and or other int casters are at or aroung 50% mana as well. If another set of 3 comes in, most likely you are not the only one pissed off at the puller.<P>I am not discrediting the chart. Never said I was, and infact it is a well informed and nice chart. I am just saying using your lesser nukes post 50 is not needed. Draughts and Tears become your bread and butter.<P>Before level 50, I did admit using lesser lines of spells (hell I did) would be prudant, but chain casting still is too dangerous no matter what your level is. Better to land your big nukes and sit down, you've done your job.<P>What I am preaching is to learn how to better the group. Nuking, and only being concerned with Nuking is not using the Wizard to it's full potential. Make assist buttons for the chanters and clerics to help them out in emergencies, and also learn that sometimes you just do not have to nuke at all.<P>--------------------<P>Baelzharon Hopeslayer<BR>Wizard of the 54th Book of Power<BR>BANG! BOOM! POOF!, Done! "WTF" you looking at? PULL SOME MORE<BR>Member of <BR> <A HREF="http://www.foreverexiled.net" TARGET=_blank>http://www.foreverexiled.net</A>
