To Qaman and Baelzharon <P>Please look at the chart again. There are only 4 places when I ever show a post 50 wizard using any spells other than drought spells ( or at least drought combined with something else ), and then I show them using Ice Commet. The only resone I sometimes show a spell combination that uses low lvl spells is to increase the damage you do per round without going oom. If you are in a post 50 group where your stun or snar spell is more important than doing 110 to 187 dmg to the mob then ofcorse you should use your stun or snar spell, you just reduce the amount of damage you do per round to compensate. I said this in my original post. I never advocated not using support spells, I just said this chart does not take them into account and that if you are using them you have to reduce your damage per round or you will find yourself going oom again.<P>To Baelzharon<P>If you are in a group pulling more than one mob at a time this chart is no longer valid as the time between fights is reduced to zero instead of 45 second. Anytime the healer going OOM you might as well be going OOM too. In these cases I totaly agree it is better to do all you can to shorten the fight time and reduce damage without over agroing.
