<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
To Arlina <P>  <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Just a thought... what happens if (when?) people you group with find out that you're manipulating them into thinking you're contributing more than you really are? Or at very least understand how a good wizard plays and thinks you're playing incompetently?<HR></BLOCKQUOTE>  <P>I hope this post was not directed at me regarding my chart. If it was directed at me, I think there is some kind of confusion here. The stratagy I presented here is not "the spectical". I only used that stratagy to illustrate how little most other players in pick up groups know about what a wizard is doing. I do not aprove of "the spectical" stratagy and I think that anyone who uses " the spectical" stratagy must have totaly given up on the class.<P>The stratagy I presented here does give up some damage over time capability in exchange for participating in ever pull but not that much.<P>Here are some calculation<P>LvL 50 Wiz casting for most damag per hour in a group with a 45 second pull time fighting mobs with 6000hp in a group with 4 tanks averaging 25dps.<P>Wizard casts 1 IC each every time they are FM then meds back to FM before casting again.<P>Mana cost = 400<BR>Regen rate = 23<BR>Time to regen mana = 400/23 * 6 = 104.34 seconds<P>Total damag per round that wiz participates = 1120<BR>Damag left for tanks to do 6000-1120 = 4880<BR>4 tanks dps = 25*4 = 100dps<BR>Total fight time = 48.8 seconds<BR>Fight time plus pull time = 48.8+45 = 93.8 seconds<P>Now subtract the med time from the fight plus pull time = 104.34 - 93.8 = 10.54 seconds<P>Each pull you lose 10.54/6 * 23 = 40 mana<P>Every ( 400/40 = 10 ) 10 pulls you will mis one fight to make up the lost mana ( if you dont want to go oom )<P>We will assume that you want to do the most damage so you will let your self gradually go oom.<P>If you have 2100 mana it would take ( 2100/40 = 52.5 ) pull before you were compleatly oom if you choose not to sit though any fights.<P>In one hour ( 60*60 = 3600 seconds) this group will kill a maximum of ( 3600/93.8 = 38 ) 38 mobs and you would have lost ( 40*38 = 1520 ) 1520 mana leaving you with 580 mana in your pool; at this point if you get some kind of over pull you can only cast IC once or cast Evac but not both.<P>Max damage possible is 38*1120 = 42560dmg<P>Ok now look at that same group where you are casting a combination of Rend and Frost shock ever pull.<P>Spell combo damage = 971<BR>Spell combo mana cost = 390<P>Med time needed is 390/23*6 = 101.74 seconds<P>Fight time is (6000-971)/100 = 50.29 seconds<P>Fight time pluss pull time is 45+50.29 = 95.29 seconds<P>Each pull you will lose ( (101.74-95.29)/6*23 = 24.73) 24.73 mana.<P>As before if you want to maintain near a full mana pool you can choose to med though a fight ever time you lose more than 390 mana. That would require that you sit though one fight after every ( 390/24.73= 15.77 ) 15 fights<P>However we will assume that you are still trying to maximize damage<P>This group can kill a maximum of (3600/95.29 = 37.77 round down to 37 ) 37 mobs per hour.<P>At the end of the hour you will have lost ( 24.73 * 37 = 915.01 ) 915 mana leaving you with 1185 mana. This is over half your mana pool and will alow you to cast at least 2 ICs and still have the mana needed to evac.<P>The max damage you could do this way is 37*971 = 35927dmg<P>If you would have been trying to maximize your damage over time you would have done 42560dmg instead of 35927dmag and the group as a whole would have only killed 1 more mob. Using this stratagy you do (35927/42560 = 0.8441 ) 84% of the damage you would have done before and you kill ( 37/38 = 0.9737 ) 97% of the mobs you would have before. However by reducing the amount of damage you do each round sightly you will now have more mana at any given time to help on an over pull, which is the real value of the wizard class in a standard exp group.<P>In both cases you could med though a fight a regular intervals to maintain you mana pool at more than 70% at all times but by using this stratagy you will miss less fights over all.
</FONT>
